To pay or not to be paid… As a veteran lead artist for over 20 seasons, I hope this helps you.

The wifi here isn’t great- so here’s a recap: 

I’ve been leading shows for NYFW for 10 years for brands @essie @cndworld @mtmorgantaylor and @nailsinc. 

There are official NYFW shows, and shows that aren’t official - they just happen the same week. 

The biggest brands never ask you to pay. They PAY YOU. They also supply you with everything you need - polish, etc. That’s the whole point: to see their brands used backstage and on the runway.

If you want to pay - what are you getting out of it - bragging rights? Ask yourself this, and other questions like who is the nail polish sponsor? What is the show? Etc. 

Shows aren’t easy. You run all over the place, sit on the floor under tables, and your work (with POLISH! Not gel) has to be perfect.

Ask me your questions below. #nyfw #nyfashionweek

latestPosts.caption:
My beach day in Antibes turned into a valuable marketing lesson that I wanted to share with you! 

Next to me, a precious 4/5 year old little girl was playing in the sand while mom watched, and a photographer came by. He asked mom if he could take her photo. (No creepers, I could tell he was legit). She said yes and he got what I am certain were gorgeous photos of the little girl. He was really good with her. He gave mom a business card and walked away. 

About 30 mins later, another photographer came by and saw the little girl and asked mom if she could take some photos of her. It was in French but I could tell she explained that she just got pics from another photographer. 

But whatever this photographer said to mom convinced her to allow her to take her photo as well.

Only this time, she took some pics with mom and daughter together, she took her hair down, etc. Variety! 

I guarantee that mom bought photos from BOTH photographers that day. 🌞 

So my lesson for you is: 
1. Don’t automatically just give up- if someone says they already have something, what can you do to show that what you offer is different? 

2. Just ask - just because someone already has a nail tech, hairstylist, makeup artist doesn’t mean that their tech isn’t traveling soon, going on maternity leave soon, and is looking for a backup or another option. Don’t assume! (But this doesn’t mean stealing clients lol)

3. Offer something unique to THEM - both of these photographers essentially would deliver the same product - photos of the little girl. But the second photographer asked what kinds of photos the first one took, then gave mom a different option.

latestPosts.caption:
Amal Clooney 🤍 for the Tony’s wearing @essie gel in “pre-show jitters” - a full coverage white with a hint of pink to soften it 🌸  #essiepartner 

Edited to add: that is my hand :) 

Get the look: 

1. I started with a manicure and filed her natural nails into a soft square shape in a medium length for maximum impact 
2. After the massage, I prepped the nail using 91% isopropyl alcohol
3. Using essie gel in “pre-show jitters”, I applied two coats 
4. Apply a coat of gel couture top coat, capping the free edge for the longest lasting mani 
5. After drying, apply essie apricot cuticle oil for a hydrated finish 

With @dimitrishair 
Wearing @tamararalph
